Dialogue: Great. Great. Thank you. And goodbye. Goodbye forever!
I have just been given the all-clear.
Yes, O beast of the southern wild!
I can finally breathe. Honestly I feel like this nine-hundred-pound
gorilla has finally stopped fucking me.
Uh-huh. And now it’s gone. Poof! I think I’m good. Greg. Me. The
circle’s tight.
Greg’s a disciple. He’s Matthew, Mark, Luke, John, Paul, George and
fucking Ringo all rolled into one.
Now I hate to be Groomzilla but can we talk venues? Because I really
like Lake Como but I’m worried about fog?
So shall we just go very, old-New York classy?
You what?
Excuse me? Shiv? What the fuck?
‘Just the wedding’? Shiv?
Okay. Fine. Let’s talk about it tonight. Let’s cuddle up here in our PJs
and talk it all out over a Thai and a Gewürztraminer, yes?
Sweetheart, no fine. If you need to think about your commitment to
Joyce then do it, go. Go to Washington. I get it. I do. Slide her under
the X-ray machine, baby!
Hey, man.
Everything okay, Greg?
Good. Because you know you can talk to me about anything?
Okay, listen. Shiv’s going to Washington. How about tonight I – take
you out?
No?
No, Greg, I’m not some beast!
Oh dear lord, no.
No it isn’t, Greg. I mean it might taste delicious to you, but it’s not.
Well it’s not how you’re supposed to like it. Look, you probably have
quite an undereducated palate. But come out, I’ll teach you. I’ll show
you how to be rich. It’ll be fun!
You should see the other guy!
Let’s just say – I was in bed with Shiv.
No, it can just get a little hot and heavy. A little freaky-deaky.
So, what’s going on? Clue me in.
Okay, well, later. I’m gonna show the country cousin how to live in
the city on under ten thousand dollars a day!
Well, hey. Gotta be done. I just keep on chowing down.
You got it, brother.
You got it.
Exactly. When I had their monkfish I thought I was going to shit, puke
and cum all at once.
Well you better find one quick. Because this is one of the most
exclusive pop-ups in the city and we’re having the full tasting menu.
Because they’re obscene.
Now, Greg? How would you handle this?
So, couple of little tips for you. Ask! Only hicks pretend to know.
Display your ignorance. It’s his problem not yours.
Two glasses of whatever will go perfectly please.
Why should we worry? If we don’t like it, it’s his fucking problem!
Look. Here’s the thing about being rich: it’s fucking great. It’s like
being a superhero only better. You can do whatever you want, the
authorities can’t touch you and you get to wear a costume but it’s
designed by Armani and doesn’t make you look a prick.
Ortolan.
It’s a deep-fried songbird. You eat it whole.
Be cool. This is a rare privilege. It’s kind of illegal!
For the head. The exact purpose is debated. Some say it’s to mask the
shame. Or heighten the pleasure.
My god. So good.
Did you eat it yet, Greg?
Eat it, Greg.
Yeah?
It’s that brainy, gamey hit, my friend.
Thank you.
Songbird bros.
Hahaha! Yes. I am! Hahaha. Because the things we’ve done, the
things we’ve seen. We’re in this together, right?
No. No, man, no. Well, I mean, look, we have a bond, but also – I
recognize myself in you.
Sure. I was an outsider once. A young guy from St Paul, alone in the
big city. And it was hard. You have to know where to go and what
wines to drink and what suits to wear and you have to wear this hard
shell but really we’re little nudie turtles.
Your grandpa’s – in New York? What for?
Are you serious?
You’re gonna want to hear. Ewan is in town. He knows and he’s come
to vote.
Can’t reveal my sources.
But it’s Greg. Greg is my source. We’re having dinner. He just saw
Ewan.
No way, hombre. My lips are sealed.
Not a big deal. Team Kendall.
Greg. It’s happening. The troops are taking Saddam’s palace. This
time tomorrow, you and me …
I could be like … the third most important man in the company.
No need. It’s bottle service. I ordered vodka.
Uh-huh, drink up. It’s two thousand bucks a pop.
Financial self-harm. It hurts a little to let you know you’re alive.
Come on, Greg! We’re celebrating!
Drink the gold, my friend. Then later, you and I will take a twenty-
four-karat piss!
Hey.
I think someone poisoned me. I’m working from home.
Thank you. You were away like fourteen hours?
What? What’s happened.
Has it happened?
It’s happened?
Yes. What’s happened? Has it happened?
Fuck. Okay?
I tried to call you.
And Kendall?
